	abstract = {This paper addresses target detection scenarios requiring high sensitivity by designing and implementing an 8channel digital phased array radar system based on the softwaredefined radio chip AD9361. The digital phased array radar features a calibration channel capable of automatic amplitude and phase consistency correction for transmit and receive channels. Utilizing a combination of MIMO and digital beamforming, the radar can simultaneously generate multiple independent beams, enabling more flexible beam steering. This system holds significant potential for applications such as target detection and tracking.},
